.TH JTUTIL-GH-BUILD "1" "June 2026" "jtutil-gh-build manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-gh-build \- Run a remote GitHub FPGA build and download the artifact
.SH DESCRIPTION
Triggers the compile-one GitHub Actions workflow for a core and
comma-separated target list, waits for the run to finish, and downloads the
matching release artifact into $JTROOT/release.
.PP
The GitHub CLI
.BR gh (1)
must be installed and authenticated with access to the jtcores GitHub
repository. The workflow file must already exist on GitHub's default branch for
manual
.B workflow_dispatch
runs to be accepted.
.PP
The target list is passed with
.B -t
or
.B --target
as a comma-separated pflag string slice. Common examples are:
.IP
jtutil gh-build cps3 -t mister,pocket
.IP
jtutil gh-build cps3 --target sidi,sidi128
.IP
jtutil gh-build cps3 -t mist
.PP
The
.B mist
target uses the Quartus 13 Docker image in the remote workflow and cannot be
combined with other targets.
.PP
After the remote run finishes successfully,
.B jtutil gh-build
downloads the matching release artifact, such as
.BR release-mister-pocket-cps3 ,
creates
.B $JTROOT/release
if needed, and extracts it there.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil gh-build <core> [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
help for gh-build
.TP
.BR \-\-ref " string"
Git ref that contains the workflow file
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-target " strings"
Comma-separated list of FPGA targets
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose
